menu "Sensors Local"

    config SENSORS_LOCAL_WEATHER_EXAMPLE_DRIVER
        bool "Enable example WEATHER local sensor driver (random values, no hardware)"
        default y
        help
            Registers a fake weather sensor ("wx-example") that feeds random
            wind/temperature/humidity/pressure/rain/luminosity readings into
            the pipeline. Useful to exercise the Weather page's channel
            picker and the WX beacon encoder with no hardware attached.
            Disable once a real weather sensor driver is in place.

    config SENSORS_LOCAL_TELEMETRY_EXAMPLE_DRIVER
        bool "Enable example TELEMETRY local sensor driver (random values, no hardware)"
        default y
        help
            Registers a fake telemetry sensor ("tlm-example") that feeds
            random analog/digital channel values into the pipeline. Useful
            to exercise the Telemetry page's channel picker with no
            hardware attached. Disable once real telemetry sensor drivers
            are in place.

    config SENSORS_LOCAL_BMP180_DRIVER
        bool "Enable BMP180 I2C WEATHER sensor driver (temperature + pressure)"
        default y
        help
            Registers a real weather sensor ("bmp180") for the Bosch BMP180
            digital barometric-pressure / temperature sensor over I2C. The
            SDA/SCL pins are fixed at build time in BMP180.h (default GPIO21
            = SDA, GPIO22 = SCL) and are excluded from every GPIO picker in
            the web admin so they cannot be reassigned to another peripheral.
            Requires the esp-idf-lib/bmp180 managed component.

endmenu
